OL,6,FDetective Chief Inspector Matthew
OL,7,FBriggs, of Dyfed-Powys Police, said:
OL,8,F"The victim in this case has shown
OL,9,Fimmense courage throughout the
OL,10,Finvestigation, and I commend her for
OL,11,Fthat. Suffering such an attack in your
OL,12,Fown home is unimaginable, and ` as she
OL,13,Fdetailed in her statement ` has
OL,14,Fimpacted every aspect of her life.
OL,15,FDespite this, she has demonstrated her
OL,16,Fstrength of character every step of
OL,17,Fthe way and worked alongside officers
OL,18,Fto ensure justice prevailed. I would
OL,19,Falso like to highlight the actions of
OL,20,Fher relative who intervened during the
OL,21,Fassault, putting their own safety at
OL,22,Frisk to ensure further harm was not
OL,23,Fcaused."
